description:
DAMSEL (?) IN DISTRESS

The cross-dressing Hato has captured the hearts of everyone in the Genshiken, but the sudden appearance of a beautiful “girl” in the otaku club raises suspicions among the student council members. A knight in shining armor steps in to save Hato… Yoshitake’s big brother! But he has secrets of his own…
name: Damsel (?) in Distress

description:
What's in a Name?

When Chitoge transfers into Raku's class, they're forced into a false love relationship to keep the peace between their feuding gangster families. Everyone at school's fooled by their act—even Raku's crush, Onodera! Raku wants Onodera to know the truth, but he just can't seem to find a way to tell her. Meanwhile, the ever-vigilant Claude sends his protégé Tsugumi to watch over Raku and rescue Chitoge from his evil intentions. What chance does Raku stand against a highly trained assassin?!

Making Sure

It's hate at first sight when Raku Ichijo first meets Chitoge Kirisaki. But much to their chagrin, the two are forced into a false love relationshio to keep the peace between their feuding gangster families. Meanwhile, Raku's still hung up on the girl he made a promise to ten years ago, keeping a pendant around his neck as a memento. The girl, in turn, holds the key that opens the pendant. To Raku's surprise, he discovers two girls have keys from a promise they also make ten years ago, Chitoge and his current crush Onodera! Making matters worse, another girl with a key appears on the scene...

  • Chapter 27: Detour

Typhoon

It's hate at first sight when Raku Ichijo first meets Chitoge Kirisaki. But much to their chagrin, the two are forced into a false love relationship to keep the peace between their feuding gangster families. Meanwhile, Raku's still hung up over the girl he made a promise to ten years ago, keeping a pendant around his neck as a memento. The girl, in turn, holds the key that opens the pendant. To Raku's surprise, he discoveres three girls have keys from a promise they also made ten years ago-Chitoge, his current crush Onodera, and the police chief's daughter Marika!

person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Chas travels to New York to address the United Nations, but the search for international support for his fledgling nation makes for strange enemies and even worse allies. Meanwhile, Zoe infiltrates the 'Green-X' eco-terror group and learns some disturbing truths about Chas and his efforts to develop the garbage patch.
name: Nation Building Part Four

description: Before they can say good-bye to London, Batman and Robin have one more villain to track down--the Clock King. What untimely mischief does this chronological criminal have in store for the revered tower of Big Ben?
name: The Clock King Strikes!

person_credits.name: Sakura Kinoshita
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, inker, colorist, cover

description: DC Comics Digital Sneak Peeks for 9/18/13.

The Man Without Fear heads out to the Left Coast in a quest to earn back the love of Miss Karen Page - and L.A.'s never been stranger! A cast of bizarre and action-packed enemies stands between DD and the woman he loves - including Stunt-Master, Brother Brimstone and the Stilt-Man. Back in the Big Apple, Daredevil teams up with the Black Panther, fights Tagak the Leopard Lord and protects a young boxer under the wing of his father's trainer. Meanwhile, the Tribune attempts to lay down his own justice on the youth movement. And it all leads to a crossover classic as DD joins forces with Iron Man and Nick Fury against Spymaster and the Zodiac! Collecting DAREDEVIL (1964) #64-74 and IRON MAN (1968) #35-36.
name: Volume Seven

description: The hit, epic series about a sinister boarding school and the kids trapped there, trying to solve the mysteries of time and space-presented once again in the beautiful, oversized deluxe hardcover format, and including copious bonus materials-sketches, character designs, cover galleries, and more! Collects MORNING GLORIES #13-25.
name: Volume 2

description: The time-displaced young X-Men continue to adjust to a present day that's simultaneously more awe-inspiring and more disturbing than any future the young heroes had ever imagined for themselves. As Jean Grey pushes her powers to the limit, shaking her and the rest of the X-Men to the core, one of the young X-Men breaks rank - and leaves to join the adult Cyclops and his revolutionary crew! And when Mastermind targets the young Jean, will history repeat itself? Plus: When the teens find themselves face-to-face with the Uncanny Avengers, young Cyclops meets the adult version of the brother he thought he'd never see again! They never warned us about this sort of thing in temporal mechanics class! Acclaimed writer Brian Michael Bendis further defines the future - and the past - of the X-Men! Collecting ALL-NEW X-MEN #11-15.
name: Volume 3

volume.name: All-New X-Men: Out of Their Depths

description: Spinning out of the hit CW television series ARROW comes these digital-first adventures! These new stories from ARROW #1-6 and #1 SPECIAL EDITION fill in the gaps between episodes of one of TV's hottest new series!
name: Volume 1

description: Batwoman's search for Medusa brings her together with Wonder Woman in these stories from issues #12-17 and #0, but even this team might not be enough to bring down the mythological monster, as Bones, the DEO, Abbot and the Religion of Crime all descend on Gotham City to take part in the fight.
name: Volume 3

description: The world didn't seem to need a man like Harry Exton anymore. An ex-soldier and mercenary, Harry was a human-killing machine without a vocation, until an old colleague told him about 'The Game.' The players, known as 'Button Men,' are paid to fight to the death in a modern-day gladiatorial contest. Organised by mysterious backers known as 'Voices,' the killing game offers bountiful financial rewards - if you live. Harry decides to participate, but soon discovers that death offers the only way out!
name: GN

description: In 1965, a strange family of outcasts made their debut in the pages of FANTASTIC FOUR. The uncanny Inhumans quickly became more than just another set of adversaries - and they all but took over and made the magazine their own! The mysterious origins of Black Bolt, Medusa, Gorgon, Triton, Karnak, Crystal and Lockjaw were revealed month after month until reader demand gave them their own feature in THOR! Now, the story of the Inhumans and their wondrous, secret land Attilan is collected from the very beginning! From Medusa's debut as a member of the Frightful Four to the battle to break the Great Barrier, it's all here in incomparable Stan and Jack fashion! Collecting FANTASTIC FOUR (1961) #36, #38, #41-47, #54, #62-65 and ANNUAL #5, plus portions of #48, #50, #52 and #55-61; and material from THOR (1966) #146-152.
name: TPB

volume.name: The Inhumans: The Origin of the Inhumans

description: Things are looking grim for Tony Stark. A string of battles with Diablo, the Serpent Squad and AIM have worn him out - and when rival industrialist Obadiah Stane targets Stark International for a very hostile takeover, the urge to crawl back into the bottle becomes overwhelming. With Tony in no condition to defend his company, his most loyal friend must step up to bat. That's right: Jim Rhodes takes over as Iron Man! But Rhodey had better figure out how to use Tony's armor fast - because Stane, Magma, Thunderball, Firebrand and more aren't going to give him time to learn the ropes! And while Rhodey endures his trial by fire, can Tony stop his self-destructive spiral before it's too late? Guest-starring Captain America, Moon Knight, Black Panther, Machine Man and Nick Fury! Collecting IRON MAN (1968) #158-177 and ANNUAL #5.
name: Volume 10

first_appearance_objects.name: Iron Man Stealth Armor Mk. I

object_credits.name: Iron Man Stealth Armor Mk. I

volume.name: Iron Man Epic Collection: The Enemy Within

description: Sinestro, Gorilla Grodd, Captain Cold and other villain star in tales of evil from SECRET SOCIETY OF SUPER-VILLAINS #1-10 and THE AMAZING WORLD OF DC COMICS #11.
name: Volume One

volume.name: The Secret Society of Super Villains

description: Henry Tanner returns to destroy Stormwatch from within in these stories from STORMWATCH #0 and 13-18! When Apollo and Midnighter go missing, one of the Shadow Lords reveals a mystery, one that will shock the team to its core! And when Etrigan finds himself in modern times, Stormwatch will be put to the test and brought to the breaking point.
name: Volume 3

description: It begins with a series of unsettling dreams, but Wolverine's nightmares soon become reality: The Weapon X Program, the sadistic agency that implanted his Adamantium skeleton, has returned! Accused of killing a senator and imprisoned, Wolverine is 'rescued' by Weapon X - but what's really going on? Which other faces from Wolverine's past are being targeted for forcible recruitment? And what is the disturbing secret of Weapon X's new director? Plus: Wolverine faces Mr. X, a martial-arts master with a fetish for death and an obsession to become 'the best there is;' battles his dead mentor Ogun; and deals with the threats of Mauvais and the Wendigo! But can a powerless Wolverine defeat the team of Sabretooth, Omega Red and Lady Deathstrike? Guest-starring Alpha Flight and the Beast! Collecting WOLVERINE (1988) #159-176 and ANNUAL 2000-2001.
name: TPB

first_appearance_locations.name: New Charles Xavier School for Mutants
Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning
New Charles Xavier School for Mutants

volume.name: Wolverine: The Return of Weapon X

deck: Captain Zero's Cavaliers try to solve the murder of their leader while being suspects themselves.
description: Summit City's most celebrated citizen, Jonathan Argos, happens to also be it's most celebrated hero, Captain Zero, leader of the Cavaliers. When Jonathan Argos is apparently the victim of a violent murder, his teammates make a decision in the heat of the moment to cover up the truth about who he was in order to protect their own identities. The team must now cover up the disappearance of Captain Zero, while also trying to help the authorities solve his murder.

deck: Plus Ultra is introduced in this issue of Overground Comics' Presents, where she learns a little about herself.
name: Plus Ultra

deck: The first graduating class of a new school for young superheroes is attacked by a mysterious villain, and who survives?  Natalie Worthy, the one student who didn't even want to be there.
description:
Does having great power always have to mean accepting great responsibility? Natalie Worthy wants to be normal, but when the rest of the world finds out that she is invincible, her privacy and her sanity may be lost to her forever!

Meet Natalie Worthy. Natalie is a member of the first graduating class of a new school for superheroes. In an attempt to drum up publicity for the school. the owners decide to fly their graduating class out to a remote location for an elaborate ceremony. Unfortunately, the plane is attacked by a mysterious man who can become living lightning. Natalie survives the attack and the resulting plane crash due to her invincibility, and is left with a choice: Escape her destiny, or fulfill it.

WIth EXCLUSIVE DIGITAL CONTENT including original art and sketches!

Grab your woods and irons, and join the Carpe DIEm Agents as they battle a haunted putt-putt gold arena - where deadly surprises wait in every hole!
name: 9 Iron

description: SERIES FINALE! When is a quarantine camp no better than a prison? Remy and her friends plan to rescue Max from the medical wing - but the consequences for them if they're caught are terrible! Who will escape? Who will stay? And in a shocking twist, who will sacrifice everything? As we come to the end of this enhanced adaptation of Amanda Hocking's best selling novel HOLLOWLAND by #1 New York Times bestseller Tony Lee (X-Men Unlimited, Doctor Who), and Steve Uy (Avengers Initiative, JSA Classified)!
name: Endgame

volume.name: Amanda Hocking's The Hollows: A Hollowland Graphic Novel

description:
Stepbrothers Orochi and Kichiro must put aside their differences to battle the vampire invasion before the sun can rise to be their savior. But will daylight truly bring the safety they so desperately seek?

Note: the digital edition was released on 09/18/2013 while the printed release was on 10/016/2013
name: (of 5)

description: With the key to turning her family back to normal in her hands, Thomasina faces a difficult choice. If she saves her family, Sebastian will turn back into a snake. If she doesn’t, her family may be stuck as animals forever. With everyone pulling her in different directions, can Thomasina make a decision before it’s too late?

Under the influence of Portia's Ooshoosh pheromones, Nez decides to leave for Ooshoosh Island to get hitched! Gina catches wind of Portia's man-jacking and pursues. Unfortunately, the island borderlands are right in the middle of a zilla-migration season, so Gina has to sneak her way past a herd of giant monsters and avoid their predators before Nez can say 'I do!'

INFINITY enters the digital realm! On the far-off Skrull planet of Hy’lt Minor, a single being stands before the awesome power of the armada of the Builders: the Silver Surfer! But will even the Surfer’s Power Cosmic be enough to save as much as a single person from the unrelenting onslaught of the Builders’ inexorable army of Aleph killing machines?
name: Against the Tide Conclusion

description: Following unexpected treacheries in Subterra and in Stone Corp., both groups prepare for war. In light of this, 034 must decide if he will utilize his capabilities to aid in the emergency evacuation of the citizens or stand with his friends in battle and embrace the killer within so that more might live.

When Chad and John, two film-obsessed vampires, realize that modern movies are ruining the reputation of their kind, they hit the town armed with a video camera and a plan... to create their own reality horror movie that gives vampires their fangs back.

Logan has reached Las Vegas, but he isn't there for the glitz and glamour.

Far from the casinos and neon lights is a world of trailer parks and tumbleweeds - a world Logan wants to call home.

Looking for a way to make ends meet, Logan finds work as an extreme fighter, taking out his aggressions for pay in abandoned warehouses and backwoods bars.

But for Wolverine, new trouble is always on the horizon...
name: Extreme Logan Part One

description: Benny and Penny hide every toy and tell Cousin Bo he can’t play with them. Will the three mice find a way to play without something getting torn, ripped, or snatched away? Geoffrey Hayes, the uncontested master of children's comics, thrills us with this hilarious tale of tiny cousins who discover a game that can’t ever be ruined.
name: GN

volume.name: Benny and Penny in the Toy Breaker

description: Reprint Walking Dead volume 1 in Serbian.
name: Davno Prošlo Vreme

description: Reprint Walking Dead volume 2 in Serbian.
name: Što Dalje

description:
Madame Adolphine is a kind, gentle old lady, and a good friend of the super-strong Benny Breakiron. So why is she robbing a bank, banging a man on the head with a mallet, and being thrown in the trunk of a car, with no memory of what happened? It's up to Benny to get to the bottom of it . . . and stop it if he can.

Note: The digital edition (9/18/2013) for this volume was released a week before the print edition (9/25/2013)
name: Madame Adolphine

description: Unscrupulous drama critic Arthur Yates finally seizes the opportunity to meet his favorite actor - the reclusive Vincent Hollow, whose legendarily realistic makeup techniques are unmatched. But the meeting takes a dark turn when Yates, eager to expose the secrets behind the makeup, attempts a friendly case of blackmail. Written and illustrated by Justin Sane!
name: No Small Parts, Act One

deck: As the only Chambers left on the crooked cops' hit list, Denise must stay alive long enough to figure out who's gunning for her.
description: Part 2 of 4. Narcotics Officer Denise Chambers comes from a family of law enforcers. Now, someone is picking them off one by one, and she'll have to figure out who's taking an axe to her family tree before it's too late.

The thing about monster hunting that no one ever contemplates is; what happens if you actually find a monster?

Down there in the darkness, deeper than any human was ever supposed to go, the Nektons have found the unexpected... and it has found them.

You demanded answers, and you get 'em with the 28 page oversized Ehmm Theory #3! Who is pulling Saint Peters strings? What is Gabriel's final task? Who is the mysterious Tym and why is he important to Gabe's father? All this and more as Gabe, Mr. Whispers & Alyona battle an unlikely and powerful foe!

Note: The digital edition (9/18/2013) for this issue was released before the print edition (10/2/2013).
name: The Cat, Quantum & Contrition Part Three

description: Evil Inc is a corporation run for super-villains by super-villains. In this monthly comic, all of the Jan. 2013 comics are released in advance as part of one download. In this issue, Captain Heroic takes his family on a road trip vacation. Also included in this edition is a Tale from the Evil Inc Archive special: Captain Heroic, disguised as Dark Hood, finds himself in control of Evil Inc and tried his best to run the evil corporation in a scrupulous way.
name: One of the Family Pt 3

description:
CHAPTER FOUR - "He Started A War" (Part 1 of 2)

George tries to get some answers from the cult, while Hank starts to enjoy being "The New Blessed One." Meanwhile, Emma confronts Atlian for some answers of her own, starting with who the traitor is on her team.
name: He Started A War Part 1 of 2

description: Antimony confronts Jones about who and what she truly is.
name: The Stone

description: From the Shuster award winning creators of Least I Could Do and Gutters comes a loving nod to classic fantasy novels that manages to flip the genre on it's head. Unlikely heros cut a swath through a fantasy world that is extremely familiar and yet very different. A naive elven hunter makes an strange friend in an undead warlock and the two manage to make both enemies and friends as they fight the good fight against the Legaran Empire.

Collects Misadventures of Adam West: Ongoing #5-9.

The Bat, The Cat and the Spaceman. Adam West is back and off to trying to get back to the present. The television's original caped crusader has finally found his way back to Earth. The only problem is that the year is 2512! Featuring Battlestar Galactica's Dirk Benedict and Julie Newmar!
name: Volume 3

description: Young actress Aria Quinn wakes up in a luxurious bedroom having no recollection of how she got there. Weirdest of all, she's chained to an iron ball, and soon enough, she will discover that she has just become the slave of her biggest fan. A sadistic, old man.
name: I Got Ball of Steel

description: Abigail, Jon, and Tanner catch Quinn's trail - only to find Quinn's survival in question! Time is running out as our heroes desperately struggle to get some answers, with strange creatures and surprises around every turn! The thrilling creator-owned sensation by Jeremy Dale (GI Joe, Marvel KaPow!, NFL RushZone) continues!

Once again featuring two stories in two different genres, Tiger Lawyer #3 continues the madness in a special 37 page issue.

Tiger Lawyer #3 features the original stories "Tiger Lawyer Must Die," the shocking conclusion to the noir story arc that started in issue #1, with art from Vic Malhotra and Adam Metcalfe, and "Grampappy Lawyer, will you please tell us the story of the shaved goat again?" with art from Matt McCray.

What do the depths of Warea hold for Hayden Griffin and his compatriots? There is a battle brewing in the depths of Virga and how much of it is centered around Aubri, the mysterious Armorer? Secrets and lies are revealed as we dive headlong into the next chapter of Virga: Sun of Suns!
A new ally joins our heroes as the adventure continues.

volume.name: War of the Woods: Season Two

description: Collects the first 4 issues of AOD: Ashes to Ashes by writer Andy (Danger Girl) Hartnell artist Nick Bradshaw and finisher Etienne St-Laurent! Features a complete cover gallery including all 4 photo covers and art covers from: J. Scott Campbell Marc Silvestri Ben Templesmith Greg Land Richard Isanove Nick Bradshaw Aaron Lopresti Michael Avon Oeming Ale Garza and Tim Seely! And finally as a special bonus Dynamite is reprinting the Newsarama interviews with series creators Nick Bradshaw and Andy Hartnell!
name: TPB

description: The tables are turned on the worlds most beautiful-and most vicious-assassin. Gunned down, comatose in a city hospital for months, and with no clue to her identity, she eventually awakens. Fully recovered but with no memory and few clues to her past, she sets out on a dangerous journey to discover who she is-But will she like what she finds? Art for this special one-shot by Fallen Angel's J.K. Woodward!
name: OGN

description: It's bloodshed at the Sunshine Diner as Jack and John James begin their southern road trip of revenge. Meet the brothers James and get a glimpse into the horrific events that inspired two twins to take their thirst for vengeance to the highways of America.

The Calamitous Black Devils is set during World War II and follows the exploits of an elite brigade of Army operatives-the Black Devils. The team is composed of mostly American and Canadian soldiers, joined by MI-6 and the Russian Night Witches. Their mission is to stop a top secret Nazi plot to harness a multidimensional gateway that will allow an Ancient One, Anan-Zaha, to cross over into our world. But while battling the Nazi forces, the team is pulled into another world against their will. They must fight their way through a universe at war, trying to make their way back home.

Beau Smith's latest creation explodes onto the scene! Aided and abetted by fellow comics legend Eduardo Barreto, Smith creates a tough guy for the new millennium in the form of Frank Cobb. Cobb is a former Level One Secret Service agent who has been off the radar for the last few years. When his aimless actions land him in jail, one of his former government contacts decides that it's time Cobb's special talents were put to a more productive use. In this debut Cobb story, "Off the Leash," Cobb's protective skills will be needed to save a very important witness from a sadistic Russian Mafia leader with connections to a terrorist cell.
name: TPB

description: CAPCOM's legendary action-horror video game series, DARKSTALKERS, in the inimitable UDON comics style! In this zero issue, "The Eye of Belial," the ultimate fate of Morrigan is foretold in fire and glory -- and destruction, including her own!

The happiness of the royal family of Edenbourg, waiting for a baptismal ceremony of the king's first grandchild, is broken by bad news-the king has been in a traffic accident. Princess Dominique runs to the site in search of her father, accompanied by the family's High Counsel, Marcus Kent, who offers to escort her. Her heart races, as she has admired Marcus since childhood, but he abuses her respect with harsh words. This is the first of a four-story miniseries, The Stanbury Crown: Royally Wed!
name: Vol. 1

description:
The parents of were-rat Lydia Iceron leaders of the were-rat clan, recently engineered their own demise after assuring that 1) Lydia was properly trained to survive their absence and 2) she had two friends whom she could trust absolutely. Now Lydia has inherited the Throne of Shadows, which allows its rightful heir to read his/her underlings' minds, and all the power that comes with it. There's a couple of problems, though. The first is that she doesn't WANT it. She'd prefer to take the money and run with her two friends, Moisha Rich and Romeo Ellis. The second is that several former members of the super-criminal organization Crime Syndicate-X DO want it, and are all too ready to cause Lydia and her friends any amount of pain and suffering to get it!

This collects the entire fan-favorite four-issue mini-series by GD creator Fred Perry and monster-master Craig Babiar (I Hunt Monsters, Pirates vs. Ninjas!) Don't let it get stolen from you!
name: TPB

description: Hunter Black begins his quest to find out who betrayed them, so he can have his revenge. What he discovers is that his targets might be beyond his ability...
name: Book One: Betrayer's Blood

description: Hurry the Rabbitoid Knight and his faithful starship Ollie finally have a lead on the last Cray in the known universe. Once it is captured, the universe will finally be safe from Mother's evil creations.

volume.name: Hurry: Adventures of the Rabbitoid Knight

description: iBotics takes you on a post apocalyptic journey, where the US government has created a division of its military defense called iBotics. One day, during an upgrade to the AI Robots intelligence, a virus caused a glitch which made one AI Robot go AWOL, killing citizens and turning on his creators. It is up to the group of military officials that are working on the project, like Eric David, to protect the world from destruction.

If you could have anything, what would you wish for? If the Wish is Fulfilled explores different answers to this question in six separate one-shots. Best friends struggle with love and life; a young buck chases after his not-so-doe-eyed teacher; two brothers learn about themselves and each other; an incorrigible yakuza heir and his exasperated mentor butt heads; two salarymen fall unexpectedly in love; and a lifelong friendship takes a bittersweet turn. Poignant and humorous, Tatsuki conveys the ups and downs of these young men's lives through an elegant blend of human emotions, engaging dialogue, and intricate artwork.
name: Vol. 1

description: Get a sneak peek at what's coming in fall 2013 from Image Comics! This preview contains exclusive content from exciting books like VELVET from Ed Brubaker and Steve Epting, BLACK SCIENCE from Rick Remender and Matteo Scalera, DEADLY CLASS from Rick Remender and Wes Craig, RAT QUEENS from Kurtis Wiebe and Roc Upchurch, ROCKET GIRL from Amy Reeder and Brandon Montclare, PRETTY DEADLY from Kelly Sue Deconnick and Emma Rios and SEX CRIMINALS from Matt Fraction and Chip Zdarsky.

How did the most wanted woman in the land end up in conflict with the sacred guardians of the realm? Why is Lantern Jack far from home and surrounded by enemies? Can the wasteland's greatest rock band fight-off foes on all sides and make it to the gig on time? Will the crew of the Maquet's Note survive the terrible secret of 'If'?

In Cold War's America, The Gauntlet is the only superhero ever created by men, and he is American. Being the only one ensured The Gauntlet fame, alcohol, sex and drugs; however this ruins the reputation and the advantage on the Soviet Union of one of the most powerful countries in the world and the only solution is to get rid of The Gauntlet.
name: Space and Fractions

description: Lost writer Zbyszewski's first foray into comics, a mash-up of hard-boiled police drama and horror, follows David Mears, a New Orleans narcotics cop-and zombie. Not your ordinary shambling, flesh-eating reanimated corpse, Mears became undead after a voodoo ritual ordered by a Haitian drug lord went awry. Understandably, that left him consumed with revenge. Now he's out to settle the score with the smugglers who condemned him to a life as a walking stiff.
name: OGN

description: The outside world must be so exciting! Princess Vanessa, of Volzemburg Kingdom, will become queen one day, and she's lived a life without freedom. Even when she visits New York on her royal duties, all she can do is smile elegantly and adhere to her strict schedule. As a 20-year-old young woman, she tires of her restrictive life, but with the help of a friend, she manages to escape for a few days. Walking through this exciting city, eating junk food and falling in love...all for the first time. But the clock keeps ticking and her time will soon run out!
name: Vol. 1

description: Other Worlds is a series of diverse sci-fi, monster and horror comic one-shots by writer and creator Justin Zimmerman, featuring lead artist Mike Lawrence and a variety of incredible independent talents.
name: GN
